%U A397261 2469,2658,2677,3337,3740,3983,4300,4695,5256,5440,5665,6082,7442,7587,9119,10062,11355,11700,12219,13129,14083,14106
%N A397261 Records in A093811.
%C A397261 Motivated in particular by the search (or proof of inexistence) of other fixed points of A093811, beyond x = 196, cf. A397257.
%C A397261 The indices at which these records occur in A093811 are listed in A397260.
%C A397261 The graph is highly self-similar, as illustrated by the plots up to 10^7 and up to 10^8.
%C A397261 The plot of the ratios A397261(n)/A397260(n) shows an oscillating pattern that repeats in each interval [10^k, 10^(k+1)], k >= 2, around a slightly decreasing average ratio. This average decreases by a factor of 0.9, which follows from the explanations in A397260. Namely, while the abscissa A397260 increase by a factor of 10, the values A397261 increase only by a factor of 9.
